dcterms:description: The deterministic FrozenLake environment is a non-slippery version of the classical FrozenLake gym environment, meaning that the environment always transitions into the next state according to the intended action.

dcterms:description: The Chain environment is a task where the agent has to choose the correct action k times in a row, receiving a reward of 0 for wrong actions and 1 for correct actions.
dcterms:title: Chain Environment

dcterms:creator: Thomas M. Moerland

dcterms:description: The ChainLoop environment is similar to the Chain environment but does not terminate when the agent chooses the wrong action, instead transitioning back to the initial state.
dcterms:title: ChainLoop Environment
